#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. Introduction\n"
"---------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Why metalog? Well, it is a decent replacement for sysklogd, the\n"
"package currently used in LFS to perform system and kernel logging. It\n"
"has a simpler (and yet more powerful) configuration file, supports\n"
"maximum log file size, rotates old logs, and buffers log messages in\n"
"memory (thus improving system performance).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    This hint will walk you through the installation and set up of\n"
"metalog. Please also read the metalog documentation when creating\n"
"/etc/metalog.conf; it will let you know about all sorts of options you\n"
"can use.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:40
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"2. Compiling, installing\n"
"------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    I used version 0.6 of metalog on my system, but these instructions\n"
"should be useful whichever version you have. Examine the `README' file\n"
"if you have a different version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Firstly, you need to install the PCRE library (Perl Compatible\n"
"Regular Expressions). This is available from http://www.pcre.org/ . I\n"
"used version 3.5, but again, any version should be fine. After\n"
"extracting the archive and changing to its directory, type:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:55
msgid "# CFLAGS=\"-O2\" ./configure --prefix=/usr # make # make install # ldconfig"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Now, installation of metalog is simple. Extract the archive and\n"
"change to its directory, and type:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:61
msgid "# ./configure --prefix=/usr # make install-strip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Metalog is now installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3. Creating /etc/metalog.conf\n"
"-----------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:69
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Read the metalog README for the exact rules on how to create a\n"
"configuration file. This file is a good start, however:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:72
msgid ""
"# /etc/metalog.conf # Configuration for metalog (replacement for syslog et "
"al.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:76
msgid "maxsize = 100000 maxtime = 86400 maxfiles = 3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:78
msgid "Kernel messages :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"kern\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/kernel\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:83
msgid "Authorisation messages :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"auth\"\n"
"  facility = \"authpriv\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/auth\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:89
msgid "Daemon messages :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"daemon\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/daemon\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:94
msgid "FTP, mail, news :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:99
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"ftp\"\n"
"  facility = \"mail\"\n"
"  facility = \"news\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/ftp-mail-news\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:101
msgid "Printing :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:104
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"lpr\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/printer\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:106
msgid "Security :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"security\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/security\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:111
msgid "System :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"syslog\"\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/syslog\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:116
msgid "Serious stuff :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"*\"\n"
"  minimum  = 2\n"
"  logdir   = \"/var/log/critical\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:122
msgid "# end"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    For each `logdir' mentioned in the above file, you need to\n"
"create a directory. Metalog will install some files in that directory.\n"
"The log can be accessed as $logdir/current (for instance,\n"
"/var/log/critical/current ). For the configuration file above, type:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:131
msgid ""
"# cd /var/log # mkdir kernel auth daemon ftp-mail-news printer # mkdir "
"critical security syslog"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can also delete the old log files: /var/log/*.log . I would\n"
"recommend doing this once you have rebooted the system and no longer\n"
"have sysklogd running.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:137
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"4. Changing /etc/init.d/sysklogd\n"
"--------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    In order to get metalog running instead of sysklogd, you need to\n"
"change the startup script /etc/init.d/sysklogd . You can rename this\n"
"file to metalog if you like, but I had already set up the symlinks and\n"
"it was easier to edit the file. Simply copy the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:146
msgid "#!/bin/sh # Begin /etc/init.d/sysklogd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:150
msgid "# # Include the functions declared in the /etc/init.d/functions file #"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:152
msgid "source /etc/init.d/functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"case \"$1\" in\n"
"\tstart)\n"
"\t\techo -n \"Starting metalog daemon...\"\n"
"\t\tloadproc /usr/sbin/metalog -B\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:159 origin/metalog.txt:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "\t\t;;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tstop)\n"
"\t\techo -n \"Stopping metalog daemon...\"\n"
"\t\tkillproc metalog\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\treload)\n"
"\techo -n \"Reloading system log daemon configuration file...\"\n"
"\t\treloadproc metalog 1\n"
"\t\t;;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:176
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\trestart)\n"
"\t\t$0 stop\n"
"\t\t/usr/bin/sleep 1\n"
"\t\t$0 start\n"
"\t\t;;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:180
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tstatus)\n"
"\t\tstatusproc /usr/sbin/metalog\n"
"\t\t;;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:185
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t*)\n"
"\t\techo \"Usage: $0 {start|stop|reload|restart|status}\"\n"
"\t\texit 1\n"
"\t\t;;\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:187
msgid "esac"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:189
msgid "# End /etc/init.d/sysklogd"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:191
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"5. Logging to a console\n"
"-----------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Unlike sysklogd, metalog doesn't immediately write anything it logs\n"
"to disk. This means that `tail -f' doesn't really do the job anymore. I\n"
"use a shell script to print to a console, however. Add the following to\n"
"/etc/metalog.conf:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:200
msgid "# start Log to a console :"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:204
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  facility = \"*\"\n"
"  command  = \"/usr/sbin/consolelog.sh 12\"\n"
"# end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Obviously, you can change the `facility', `minimum', etc. to suit\n"
"yourself. Also, you can combine `command' and `logdir' in a single\n"
"entry. See metalog's README for more details. The `12' in the\n"
"commandline is the VT to print to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:211
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Create the /usr/sbin/consolelog.sh script like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:221
msgid ""
"# cat >/usr/sbin/consolelog.sh <<EOF >#!/bin/sh ># /usr/sbin/consolelog.sh "
"># For metalog -- log something to a console > >echo \"$2 [$3] $4\" "
">/dev/tty$1 > >EOF # chmod +x /usr/sbin/consolelog.sh"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:225
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can change the formatting of the echo command as needed; $2 is\n"
"the date, $3 is the name of the program sending the entry, $4 is the\n"
"entry text, and $1 is the VT to print to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Appendix A. Building LFS with metalog\n"
"-------------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/metalog.txt:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    This is a trivial change to make. Obviously, you no longer need to\n"
"install the `sysklogd' package. When you come to install this package,\n"
"install PCRE and then metalog instead (step 2). Rather than creating\n"
"/etc/syslog.conf and /var/log/*.log, create /etc/metalog.conf (step 3)\n"
"and its directories. Finally, don't use the LFS-provided\n"
"/etc/init.d/sysklogd script, use the one given in step 4.\n"
msgstr ""
